    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-09T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-09T16:00:00-05:00" n="405"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d405">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.5151/619: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gordon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-09T18:00:00-03:00"
                            >May 9, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 9—5:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>128. Department’s 84, May 8, 7 p.m. The <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> which
                    I submitted to the Minister of Finance last night put the matter substantially
                    in the same manner as it is set forth in the Department’s telegram under
                    reference with one exception; namely, the new point contained in the
                    Department’s telegram concerning the utilization of any balance in the annuity
                    to redeem the obligations issued by the Bank of Brazil by repayment at par under
                    precise conditions to be determined. In my <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> I
                    dealt with the necessity of the annuity taking care of the interest and
                    amortization of such obligations. If I understand correctly the Department’s
                    idea is in effect an accelerated amortization so I consider the principle
                    covered by my <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>, and can give the point the
                    desired application in my next interview with the Finance Minister.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gordon</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
